        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 6:36PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 636 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Pisgah, or near
Ellijay. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
East Ellijay, Cherry Log, Ellijay, Cartecay, Pisgah, and Roy.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
